rComments: Mrs Garaud is a very good Teacher ! Take her class !
She was a good lecturer as long as you listened during class. Tests are easy if you do her practice tests.

She uses different methods of solving a problem than i'm used to and it confuses me as to which one to choose since hers feels overcomplicated to me. She's an alright professor but she tends to go through the material quickly so keep up
She teaches good stuff, but she is not a nice person, very rude.

I've already taken pre-calculus so I thought I'd do super well. I'm doing alright but not as well as I'd anticipated. Pascale overcomplicates the subject when really there are many shortcuts you can take. Pay attention and find the strategy that works best for you. And do the practice midterms! The tests are exactly like it with the numbers changed
Simply the BEST. If you have any interest in learning math take a class with her. Explains the subject matter extremely well and her tests are very fair often with extra credit problems.

PROS- curved grades. a c is really a b, small class so feels like private school, dont need to buy a textbook just print out notes. CONS- lectures focused on case studies, explains math part in "mathmatical corner".
Great teacher easy tests and quizes just requires u to b in class all the time. Very helpful even awards extra credit during office hours. And very very good looking looks almost like a student
She got better this year in term of being nicer and teach better. However, she doesn't like to talk to students or help them.
learned a lot in her class.Her lectures actually help and homework is also helpful. Theres a lot extra credit so its pretty easy to get a b without trying extremely hard

Greatest math professor I have had so far.She wants you to ace the class.Plenty extra credit opportunities.If you work hard, you get the grade you deserve.TA's are extremely helpful.Go to lectures and sections and you should get an A or A+ (if you do the extra-credit's too).

you'll learn to like her by the end of the quarter! her teaching methods: superb! learned a lot of math in just a quarter. she's knowledgeable, helpful, and straight-forward. how to do well: pay  attention in class, attend sections, DO the homework (esp applied probs) and take advantage of her practice midterms/finals! garaud is one of the bests!

She seems very difficult at first, but her style of teaching  is really helpful. One of the only math classes were i actually learned how to do the math properly. Lots of hard work, but totally worth it

Many people are intimidated by Pascale but that is because she speaks her mind  (who wouldn't want silence while they are trying to lecture?). Great teacher, very enthusiastic, extremely knowledgeable- check out her academic background!! All in all, a very clear, precise, and worthwhile class. Especially if u plan on continuing your math ed @ ucsc

Her system of taking notes is very useful i think. Just print out the papers and take the notes..they help a lot, and you don't even need to open the book.  Her quizes, tests are kinda hard, but if you study hard you should do well ( after all 80% is an A- in this class). Homework is kinda short and prepares you for the test very well.

Scary at first. but all in all a very fair teacher. she gives back points for hw since some graders are so horrible. also gives an outline for lecture notes. PRINT THEN AND BRING THEM TO CLASS! the book it not necessary i didn't have one and i got an A-. pay attention to the applied problems on hw and exams. they're the killers!

She is a small woman but very intimidating. She lies too. There was a huge curve to account for her harsh grading. Lectures don't necessarily help. If you have a textbook you can skip them. Sections were worthless.

Though she may appear as a difficult teacher. She is truly a great teacher, she wants students to really understand calculus. And more or less does a good job doing so. She's really passionate with the subject, and it has been said that not many university professors are like her. To be honest, I think she's the best math teacher I've ever had.
She was a great teacher.  Very helpful.  Not a lot of HW.  She really wants to help her students understand the material and gives out tons of extra credit.  If you go to section, you will do well.

She comes off as one of the rudest people on the first day of lecture, but she does have her moments. It may seem impossible, but they do happen. Print out the notes, you won't be able to live w/o them and make sure you go to lecture to fill in the blanks! She definitely knows what she's talking about.

Horrible teacher, she herself understands what she's teaching but I don't feel like she's a good teacher at all. I actually became more confused on matters I had already understood fairly well. I do not feel she was helpful or that I learned anything much in this class.

Pretty fair teacher.  Paid a lot of interest into the learning of the students.  Then again it was a small class.  But was very enthusiastic nonetheless.  Kept material interesting, and not too hard if you kept up with the assignments.
Wonderful teacher, extremely interested in how her students are doing, and VERY helpful if you go to office hours or put in any effort at all.

She tried  hard with this class, put in so much of her own time, and tried to be available and helpful in office hours. Lectures however were a disaster, homework was unbearable (our ACE leader couldn't even figure out her assignments sometimes), and the final, that was about the worst test ever!

SHE IS THE MOST HORRIBLE MATH TEACHER EVER! Honest going to class everytime, doing all the homework, and doing the quizzes does not help you pass at all! Her work is much to difficult for a calc class, her test were unbearable. Dont take the class with her, I regreat it so much!!

hard teacher, but very knowledgeable and helpful if you go up to her

homework can be hard sometimes, but if you study, you'll do fine on tests and quizzes. she is a hard prof but her notes and attending sections help a lot. shes actually a pretty good professor. her notes are clear and always there to help when needed.

I had her for Math 11A and she is a REALLY good teacher. You really don't need the book at all. We barely used it. Her notes are online and you prints them out before hand and just fill them in. It's really organized. There is a really big curve, so it's in students favor. Overall, you will learn a lot in this class but prepare to work for it.

When I had Prof. Garuad all I could think of was how much I disliked her and how miserable she made winter quarter, but I learned SO MUCH!  She was a great teacher and her teaching method was fantastic.  I really wish she taught more calc classes because it was worth it.  She will try to scare you, but don't be intimidated, there's a HUGE curve

Highly recommended. The huge curve makes the class easy. Even without the curve, you would probably do well. She is very clear in explaining things. The only thing that was kind of tough was the homework, but the TAs in section help out a lot with that.

she makes you print your notes out for each class, a lot of paper but worth it.  she is always willing to help her students, but she wants you to work for your grade.. she also has applied problems that are hard, but you can work, often fight through. over all she is pretty good :)

She seems like a hard ass, but she's really not. Her curve is huge and she really is a good teacher. She gives lots of help with practice tests, extra credit, and help for those of us who still have not mastered algebra. Best Math Teacher I've had yet!

I recommend printing all the lecture notes, although they are such a waste of ink and paper. The book is unnecessary and not helpful towards her class. She is tough, but at times, can be nice. The lectures are a bit boring. One midterm and a final, both pretty difficult, but are very curved, so letter grades are, in the end, reasonable.

I thought she was a very good teacher.  Her notes made it easy to refer back to especially for the quiz.  The grading scale I wish was a little bit MORE lenient... but you get what you put in.  You'll have to take the time to REALLY study though and work it out.  Although, I hate applied problems, you need to recall on past math.

The best math teacher I've ever had.  Its a super challenging class but if you're willing to put in the effort its well worth it.  She lays all the concepts out for you in a very straightforward and clear way.  If you print out all her notes, you dont need to buy the book which'll save you money.  She also has an awesome grade scale 80% = A 60% = B

Well, her looks are deceiving.  She knows what she is doing and she is good at teaching math but her attitude is compareable to a Fire-Breathing-Dragon!!!  She will destroy you if you piss her off but her curve is very nice if the class fails.  Either study a lot or pray to god that the class has an average of 55 on the midterm.

Its a love-hate thing with Garud. I'm sure she was a navy seal or a boot camp sergeant in a previous life. She'll work you to the grave. If you get your butt in gear, you'll pull through. She is clear and straight forward. And her lectures are very helpful. Keep on your toes and practice, practice, practice.
Pascale is ruthless.  She doesn't care about her students at all.  Not clear and only creates a huge grading curve (80%=A, 60%=B) becuase she's a terrible teacher and needs to account for it somehow.

Yet, her passion for the subject is contagious!  Go to office hours and be on top of things!!  Tests are hard, but fair.  Love that accent!
Sharp as hell, keep up and she's great, but not an introductory level class teacher at all.
